I am into movies and have a decent collection going. I do not buy just anything. I must really like the movie or it has to have unique qualities about it in order for me to purchase it. When I do, I seek out the best version of it whether it is from North America or Japan. My movies range in taste from:

thoughtful dramas (eg A Beautiful Mind/What Dreams May Come) to

comedies (eg Rat Race) to

pure fantasy (eg The Matrix/Star Wars). 

Depending on the kind of day I have at work, in the evening, I play music that is the opposite of that to keep a balance in my life. For example, if I had a really hard and intense day, I play music by Enigma, Enya, Delerium, Deep Forest, or something else that is mellow and soothing. If I had a really boring day, I play progressive house, trance, or anything else that has a nice beat to it. Unofficially, I have the title of Mood Music Manager at work as I create what I like to call sonic landscapes during the day. 

I may be a techno-geek with all the stuff around me all day long, but I am also a nature lover. I like being outdoors just to feel the ocean breeze on a warm day, to smell the sweet air after the rain, to listen to the birds, to just sit in quiet contemplation. Whenever I can, I watch the kinds of shows they have on Animal Planet or PBS where animals or the outdoors is the focus, or about our surroundings in general including what is beyond our planet. 

Does it look like I enjoy eating? YouÃÆÃÂ¢ÃÂ¢ÃâÃÂ¬ÃÂ¢ÃâÃÂ¢d guess right! I like to cook and experiment with new recipes when I have time. I like trying foods from different cultures. I guess that is easy in Vancouver since there are so many restaurants of all ethnic origins and diversities. 

When it comes down to it, there is not much I don't like. I certainly HATE people that are rude, crude, insensitive, have no feelings for anyone except for themselves or those who impose their beliefs on others. I have a list of other things, but they would be too petty to mention. 

I am a pretty easy going guy and usually turn the other cheek. In the business that I am in, I have to be. If, however, someone were to push me far enough (and believe me it takes a lot to do that) be warned, I can become just as nasty and then some! 

There is also the silly side of me. I like keeping things light with humour and comedy, but when it comes to something needs to be done which requires all my resources, become focused and intense. 

I am analytical and inquisitive by nature. I want to know how things work, why things are the way they are, and what makes us who we are. 

My biggest fear is not meeting someone elses expectations when I have set out to do something through my own will, or when asked to do so. I rarely say no. Normally, it does not matter what anyone thinks about me, whether you like me, hate me, or are indifferent so long as I have not given reason for you to feel that way. If I have given someone a reason not to like me, I will try whatever I can to correct that. 

I have no expectations of anyone else except for respect and admiration so long as (s)he thinks I have earned it and not because I think I deserve it. 

I do not ask for favours or help from anyone unless, under very rare circumstances, I have exhausted all of my own resources. 

Whenever I reach one, I pause for a moment and look for the next one (unless of course it is the end of the road)
